title: Textile, 1890–1900
medium:
Medium: cotton
Technique: printed on sateen
description: Narrow length of light blue sateen printed in a highly stylized floral pattern in Art Nouveau style. Symmetrical arrangement of two open face round flowers in a rose color on rigidly drawn branching stems with small leaves in dark and light green. Larger pale green leaves are three lobed at turns of the stems. Entire design is outlined in dull red.
